result.execSummary:
The defendant Gabriel John Aguad-Baumgartner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Gabriel John Aguad-Baumgartner is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Gabriel John Aguad-Baumgartner was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
